Bringing Alpine Linux to IBM s390x machines ( Z series )

This scripts requires a cross-compiler targeting s390x (gcc coupling with musl) which can be built using https://github.com/tmh1999/musl-cross

The required cross-compiler directory tree should look like this:
# s390x-linux-musl/
#	bin/
#		s390x-linux-musl-ar
#		s390x-linux-musl-gcc
#		s390x-linux-musl-ranlib
#		...
#	s390x-linux-musl/
#		lib/
#			libc.a
#			libdl.a
#			libcrypt.a
#			...
#		bin/
#		include/
#		...
#	lib/
#	include/
#	...

To run this script:

./build.sh /path/to/s390x-linux-musl s390x-linux-musl


Successfully built:
- Alpine's apk-tools
- Busybox
